# ESLint Context (BSI)

The project uses ESLint with TypeScript and React plugins.

## Key rules (from .eslintrc.json)

### TypeScript
- `@typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any`: off (but Cursor rules prefer avoiding `any`)
- `@typescript-eslint/no-unused-vars`: warn (prefix unused with `_`)

### React
- `react/react-in-jsx-scope`: off (Next.js auto-imports)
- `react/prop-types`: off (use TypeScript instead)
- `react/no-unknown-property`: allows `jsx` and `global` props

### Console usage
- `no-console`: warn, but allows `console.warn`, `console.error`, `console.info`
- Scripts and tests: console is fully allowed

